1
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:15,125
Oh...

2
00:00:15,208 --> 00:00:17,166
[TOHRU]
Christmas, huh?

3
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:19,083
I do hate the idea of
celebrating the birth

4
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:22,041
of You-Know-Who's son,
but I gotta say,

5
00:00:22,125 --> 00:00:23,625
it sounds like a good time.

6
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:25,416
Tohru, hey!

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,791
[TOHRU]
Hey back!

8
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,083
Oh, no!

9
00:00:28,166 --> 00:00:29,375
What happened to you?

10
00:00:29,458 --> 00:00:31,041
[BUTCHER A] Unfortunately,
I was practicing for

11
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:33,500
the local retirement home's
annual Christmas Eve show,

12
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:35,375
but I ended up injuring myself.

13
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:36,916
Ah...

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
You must feel so
weak and flimsy.

15
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:40,333
Oh, hey!

16
00:00:40,416 --> 00:00:41,708
Tohru, do you think you
might be willing to put on

17
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,375
the show in my stead?

18
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:44,666
Uh?

19
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,041
The residents in the home
were looking forward

20
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:48,666
to the event, so I feel like
I'm letting them down.

21
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:50,791
Put on a show?

22
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:52,166
Are you serious?

23
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:53,416
Yes, of course.

24
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:55,500
No one could represent
our shopping district

25
00:00:55,583 --> 00:00:56,958
better than you!

26
00:00:59,083 --> 00:01:00,208
Okay, we'll do it!

27
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:02,291
And don't worry, it'll be super!

28
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:04,000
[TOHRU giggles]

29
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:37,208
[TOHRU]
And so I'm totally gonna do it!

30
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:38,333
Are you sure?

31
00:02:38,416 --> 00:02:39,708
Sure, I'm sure!

32
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:41,708
I'd like to help out,
too, but I can't.

33
00:02:41,791 --> 00:02:44,375
I have stupid work.

34
00:02:44,458 --> 00:02:46,041
That's all right,
Miss Kobayashi.

35
00:02:46,125 --> 00:02:47,416
You just stay
focused on your job,

36
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,500
and I'll take care
of everything.

37
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:51,375
Whatever. If you say so.

38
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:53,791
[TOHRU laughs]
It'll be easy.

39
00:02:53,875 --> 00:02:56,041
All I gotta do is ask my
reliable and free friends

40
00:02:56,125 --> 00:02:57,583
to help me out!

41
00:02:57,666 --> 00:02:59,000
Ready, everyone?

42
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:00,500
Let's put on a show!

43
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:01,791
[BOTH]
Yeah!

44
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:03,375
[BOTH]
Um. Yeah.

45
00:03:03,458 --> 00:03:04,458
Wait a second!

46
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:05,750
Jeez, what is it?

47
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,791
Have I been lied to?
Because I was told I could

48
00:03:07,875 --> 00:03:10,208
eat as much candy as
I wanted if I came here.

49
00:03:10,291 --> 00:03:12,000
I even made room in my
schedule even though

50
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,916
it's one of the busiest
times of the year!

51
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,833
Miss Kobayashi told me
the truth about you, Elma.

52
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:18,416
You're completely
useless at work.

53
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:19,750
Uh--

54
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,125
So much so that they've
even announced they didn't

55
00:03:21,208 --> 00:03:23,000
need you to be in
their way right now.

56
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:25,500
Ah... It doesn't make any sense!

57
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:27,541
Now I can actually
type with my fingers!

58
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,833
What else can I do when
I can't afford to interfere

59
00:03:29,916 --> 00:03:31,458
with this world?

60
00:03:31,541 --> 00:03:34,458
Believe me, you're already
interfering plenty.

61
00:03:34,541 --> 00:03:35,458
[ELMA groans]

62
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:36,458
Question.

63
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:38,208
Why isn't Kanna's
mom doing this?

64
00:03:38,291 --> 00:03:41,708
Unlike Elma, Miss Kobayashi
is busy with her work, so,

65
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:44,583
it's up to us to take
care of this on our own!

66
00:03:44,666 --> 00:03:45,958
What do ya say?

67
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:47,666
Boring.

68
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:50,000
I heard something
important was happening.

69
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:53,083
Turns out it was just
something pathetic instead.

70
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:55,166
Oh, come on, Fafnir!

71
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:57,416
Let's keep an eye
on how it goes.

72
00:03:58,583 --> 00:03:59,791
[ELMA]
Well, then.

73
00:03:59,875 --> 00:04:02,250
What exactly do you want
us to do for this show?

74
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,333
I think, to start off with,
it should probably be

75
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:06,833
something the elderly
would enjoy watching.

76
00:04:06,916 --> 00:04:07,750
That works for me.

77
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:09,208
Any other ideas?

78
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:09,833
I know!

79
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:11,333
An eating contest!

80
00:04:11,416 --> 00:04:12,208
No.

81
00:04:12,291 --> 00:04:13,833
You just wanna stuff your face.

82
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:14,833
How 'bout a race?

83
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,458
[LUCOA]
That might kill them.

84
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:20,208
We should play a VR FPS,
FFA, AKA frag fest.

85
00:04:20,291 --> 00:04:22,916
[LUCOA]
I'm sorry, could you use words?

86
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,541
But all of these ideas require
the audience to participate.

87
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:27,833
You can't judge us
when you haven't

88
00:04:27,916 --> 00:04:29,666
actually proposed anything!

89
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:32,291
Do the two of you
have any suggestions?

90
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:33,666
I'm okay with whatever.

91
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,291
Okay, so, what if
we put on a play?

92
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,666
