93
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,583
Is that where humans pretend
to be different humans

94
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,583
on a globe stage
that's not a globe?

95
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:42,875
Globe stage that's what?

96
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,750
[TOHRU]
A play, huh?

97
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,041
That's perfect!

98
00:04:46,125 --> 00:04:47,458
Let's put on a play!

99
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:49,041
Fine.

100
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:51,083
We will put on a play, but what
do you think we should put on?

101
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:54,083
Since it's Christmas time,
why not <i>The Little Match Girl</i> ?

102
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:55,291
Ooh, that sounds funny.

103
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:56,583
Is it funny?

104
00:04:56,666 --> 00:04:58,000
[SAIKAWA]
Um, no.

105
00:04:58,083 --> 00:05:00,791
It's about this poor little
girl selling matchsticks

106
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:03,416
on a very cold winter's night.

107
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:06,375
Sadly, no one will buy
any matches from her.

108
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:08,833
So, in order to warm
her chilled body,

109
00:05:08,916 --> 00:05:11,458
she lights one of the matches.

110
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:13,791
Then, in the flame,
she sees a warm stove

111
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:16,625
and lots of delicious food.

112
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:19,250
She lights match after
match, and eventually,

113
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,958
her beloved and yet
very much dead grandmother

114
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:24,291
appears to her.

115
00:05:24,375 --> 00:05:26,666
The little girl continues
lighting her matches

116
00:05:26,750 --> 00:05:29,208
to keep her grandmother
from disappearing,

117
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:33,041
until finally, the grandmother
gently hugs the little girl.

118
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:35,541
Then the little girl
ascends to Heaven,

119
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:39,208
embraced in her grandmother's
warmth and love.

120
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:41,416
It's kind of a
sad story, and gosh,

121
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:43,208
it gets me every time.

122
00:05:43,291 --> 00:05:45,375
Yeah, it's pretty famous.

123
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:46,708
Oh.

124
00:05:46,791 --> 00:05:48,708
So, what happens after the
girl ascends to Heaven?

125
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:50,291
Does she sell her matchsticks?

126
00:05:50,375 --> 00:05:51,583
Idiot.

127
00:05:51,666 --> 00:05:53,791
The girl ascends to Heaven
because she's dead.

128
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,000
Wow.

129
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:57,083
That woman strangled
her own granddaughter.

130
00:05:57,166 --> 00:05:58,083
Die!

131
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,458
[ELMA]
No, that's not it either.

132
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:01,875
You know a lot,
Saikawa. It's so cool.

133
00:06:01,958 --> 00:06:03,958
Uh-- Yeah, I guess.

134
00:06:04,041 --> 00:06:05,250
It's no big deal.

135
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:06,916
I'm good with putting on
<i>The Little Match Girl</i>

136
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,416
if you guys are!

137
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,291
[GROUP]
Yeah!

138
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:13,041
Sure hope we don't blow it.

139
00:06:13,125 --> 00:06:15,625
Fafnir will obviously
be directing.

140
00:06:15,708 --> 00:06:17,458
Keep in mind,
Fafnir will not stand for

141
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:19,458
any sophomoric performances.

142
00:06:19,541 --> 00:06:21,916
Fafnir is the
absolute authority.

143
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,958
Challenge him and
you will suffer.

144
00:06:24,041 --> 00:06:25,208
[BOTH gasp]

145
00:06:25,291 --> 00:06:27,041
Also, keep in mind
Fafnir's only the director

146
00:06:27,125 --> 00:06:28,500
because he can't act.

147
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,541
Now, come on nepotism!

148
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,375
Before anything,
Fafnir needs to cast

149
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:34,000
the lead of this play.

150
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:35,875
He wants each of you
to audition for the role

151
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:37,291
of Little Match Girl.

152
00:06:37,375 --> 00:06:39,166
Yay! I can go first!

153
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,916
Tohru, auditioning for
Little Match Girl.

154
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,208
[FAFNIR]
Just get started.

155
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:44,833
Do not disappoint Fafnir.

156
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:45,958
Matchstick.

157
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,750
Oh, please, won't
anyone buy a match?

158
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:49,333
Boring. Next.

159
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:50,541
What? Already?

160
00:06:50,625 --> 00:06:52,208
[FAFNIR]
I'll give you one more shot.

161
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:54,708
This time, see those
heartless humans ignoring you

162
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:55,833
like the trash you are.

163
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:56,541
[gasps]

164
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:57,791
[FAFNIR]
Feel it.

165
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:00,083
Then, allow the lines
to flow naturally.

166
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:02,791
[TOHRU]
Feel it, huh?

167
00:07:02,875 --> 00:07:05,333
Why, you foolish,
inferior humans!

168
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:07,916
How dare you ignore me
to suffer like this?

169
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,666
--I'll make you pay for--
--[FAFNIR] Fail. Next.

170
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:13,958
Hello, my name is Elma,
and I'm unrepresented.

171
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:15,083
Matches?

172
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,583
Do you need any matches?

173
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:17,583
I don't.

174
00:07:17,666 --> 00:07:18,458
[ELMA]
Please, sir!

175
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:20,666
Please at least hear me out!

176
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:23,541
I can't go back to the office
until I've sold them all.

177
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:25,208
[FAFNIR]
What are you doing?

178
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:27,291
The salesmen that come
to our company always

179
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:28,916
put on a performance like that.

180
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,000
[FAFNIR]
Sucks for them.

181
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:31,583
Next.

182
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:32,708
Good afternoon!

183
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:34,166
I'm Riko Saikawa.

184
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:35,583
Thank you for your time.

185
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:37,000
Ah!

186
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:39,083
I... Uh...

187
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:40,625
[SAIKAWA whimpers]

188
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:41,833
Oh, god, why?

189
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:43,666
I'm so sorry!

190
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:46,416
[FAFNIR] To be honest,
none of you are any good.

191
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:47,666
[TOHRU]
To be extra honest,

192
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:49,916
your directing style is
way too sadistic for us.

193
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,166
Ooh, me!

194
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:52,416
[TOHRU]
Yeah, you what?

195
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:53,541
[LUCOA]
Let me direct.

196
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:55,833
I can be nice and firm!

197
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:57,458
And I'll make Shouta the lead.

198
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:58,416
Uh--

199
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:00,083
What are you even talking about?

200
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:02,416
Shouta's a boy,
not a little girl.

201
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:05,083
Well, you just leave that to me.

202
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:07,250
Shouta, baby, come here.

203
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:10,500
[ALL]
Ooh...

204
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:15,958
[ELMA]
He looks just like a girl!

205
00:08:16,041 --> 00:08:17,291
[KANNA]
So cute.

206
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:18,583
[TOHRU]
Yeah, I'll buy it.

207
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:19,375
[SAIKAWA]
I dunno.

208
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:21,333
He's not as cute as Kanna.

209
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:22,041
Wha...

210
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:23,083
[ALL]
"Wha"?

211
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:24,333
What are you all
planning to achieve

212
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:25,375
--by embarrassing meee?
--[LUCOA] Shouta, baby,

213
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:26,250
--by embarrassing meee?
--come back!

214
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,875
Well, that was to be expected.

215
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:31,375
C'mon, cheer up, sweetie.

216
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:33,125
[TOHRU]
What should we do, now?

217
00:08:33,208 --> 00:08:35,208
[ELMA]
I can be the director.

218
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:37,166
I'll at least be better
than those two.

219
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:38,833
[TOHRU]
That's true.

220
00:08:38,916 --> 00:08:41,291
Any thoughts on who we
should make our lead?

221
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,208
Matches.

222
00:08:49,291 --> 00:08:50,583
Matches.

223
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,291
Please buy some matches.

224
00:08:52,375 --> 00:08:54,041
[yelps]

225
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:57,625
[squeals]

226
00:08:57,708 --> 00:08:59,625
[ELMA, TOHRU]
Mm-hm! Perfect!

227
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:05,291
[KOBAYASHI]
Hey, guys, I'm home.

228
00:09:05,375 --> 00:09:06,333
[KANNA]
Matches.

229
00:09:06,416 --> 00:09:08,750
Do you wanna buy
any matches, please?

230
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Mind filling me in?

231
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:14,500
We decided to perform
<i>The Little Match Girl</i>

232
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,541
for our show at the
retirement home.

233
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:18,875
Kanna has been cast
as the title character.

234
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:21,833
[KOBAYASHI]
Oh, I see.

235
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:24,583
Congratulations, Kanna!

236
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:26,708
[KANNA]
Mm-hm. I'm excited.

237
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:29,791
I promise to come see you.

238
00:09:29,875 --> 00:09:31,250
You sure you'll be okay?

239
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:32,750
Of course we will!

240
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,625
There's no way a play
can take down a dragon.

241
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:36,750
Right.

242
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,625
Do you want to buy
any matches, please?

243
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,291
[KOBAYASHI] She's at
her most dangerous

244
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:42,458
when she gets like this.

245
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:43,666
[KOBAYASHI]
If you say so.

246
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,875
--[KANNA] Match?
--I'm gonna go take a bath.

247
00:09:44,958 --> 00:09:46,000
--[TOHRU] 'Kay!
--Matches?

248
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,541
[phone ringing]

249
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:49,500
Coming, phone.

250
00:09:49,583 --> 00:09:51,291
Hello, Kobayashi residence.

251
00:09:51,375 --> 00:09:52,541
[FAFNIR]
It's me.

252
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:55,125
I thought about the
script some on my own.

253
00:09:55,208 --> 00:09:56,458
You're still not gonna
be the director,

254
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:58,625
so if it's that, let it go.

255
00:09:58,708 --> 00:10:00,625
Otherwise, what did
you come up with?

256
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:02,125
[FAFNIR] If we stick
