00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,583
So, I decided to make the little
match girl into a magical--

259
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:11,791
[TOHRU] All right then, time to
prepare Miss Kobayashi's dinner.

260
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,833
Do you want to buy
any matches, please?

261
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,750
Lady Tohru, is there a
chimney in this house at all?

262
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,833
Is there a chimney?

263
00:10:29,916 --> 00:10:31,375
No, why do you ask?

264
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:34,000
[KANNA] Because Saikawa told me
that Santa visits your house

265
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:35,750
by coming down the chimney.

266
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:39,125
Oh, yeah, you mean that old man
who's covered in blood?

267
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:40,541
Ho!

268
00:10:40,625 --> 00:10:42,791
[KANNA] Do you think Santa will
still try to visit us?

269
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:44,708
[TOHRU]
Hm...

270
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,000
Yes!

271
00:10:47,583 --> 00:10:48,750
[KOBAYASHI]
Hm?

272
00:10:51,458 --> 00:10:53,583
[gasps]

273
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:55,541
[KOBAYASHI]
What the crap?

274
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:04,833
[ELMA]
What are you doing?!

275
00:11:04,916 --> 00:11:05,958
No, no!

276
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:08,125
How many times do I
have to tell you?

277
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:10,291
No, where do you
think you're going?

278
00:11:10,375 --> 00:11:13,000
Tohru! Why would a rando use
Kobayashi as reason to refuse

279
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:14,166
to buy matches?

280
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,666
Yeah, well, why would
I be in a hurry if

281
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:16,958
I wasn't doing
something for her?

282
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:18,458
[ELMA]
Not my problem!

283
00:11:18,541 --> 00:11:20,833
Lucoa! The grandmother would
not try to warm the girl up

284
00:11:20,916 --> 00:11:22,041
while practically nude.

285
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:22,958
[LUCOA]
Why not?

286
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:24,625
It's much warmer this way.

287
00:11:24,708 --> 00:11:27,125
[ELMA] Fafnir, you're
completely out of line.

288
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:30,375
A human father would never call
his daughter a "mere human."

289
00:11:30,458 --> 00:11:32,041
Focus!

290
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:35,250
[ELMA] Why is accepting this
script such an ordeal?

291
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,500
[TOHRU] Well, I don't think
it translates that well,

292
00:11:37,583 --> 00:11:39,125
culturally speaking.

293
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,833
Not to mention it's
slow and repetitive

294
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:42,500
and might bore the audience.

295
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:44,916
[ELMA] True, and we don't
want that to happen.

296
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,416
Then why don't we try
changing things up just a bit?

297
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,166
What are you suggesting we do?

298
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,541
Nothing too extreme.

299
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:51,833
I mean, I think
at the very least,

300
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:53,291
we should make it more fun.

301
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:55,000
That sounds good to me!

302
00:11:55,083 --> 00:11:56,833
[TOHRU] Why don't we mix
other myths in with it,

303
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,708
like the Kasa Jizou story!

304
00:11:58,791 --> 00:12:00,916
Like we have the old man
selling hats next to the girl.

305
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,166
[ELMA]
Or we could follow the script.

306
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,833
[LUCOA]
I like it.

307
00:12:03,916 --> 00:12:06,125
[FAFNIR] The main character
should be a magical girl.

308
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:08,833
She can obtain power
to burn this corrupt world,

309
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,500
burn it to ash.

310
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:13,625
[ELMA] Now there's nothing
from the original left.

311
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:15,500
[LUCOA]
You know, I've heard <i>47 Ronin</i>

312
00:12:15,583 --> 00:12:16,916
is popular with the elderly.

313
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,458
[FAFNIR]
Oh, yes, the one about humans

314
00:12:18,541 --> 00:12:20,208
and their quest for revenge.

315
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:21,375
I can appreciate that.

316
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:22,958
[KANNA]
Are there any dragons?

317
00:12:23,041 --> 00:12:26,250
[LUCOA] We might as well have
some while we're at it, right?

318
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,500
[ELMA]
Hey, Grandma!

319
00:12:27,583 --> 00:12:29,583
Stop making it sexy!

320
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:31,833
Narrator, stop grinning
like an idiot!

321
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,250
[TOHRU]
Kanna.

322
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,416
From what I've heard, this
Santa guy won't be coming by

323
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,833
for a little while longer.

324
00:12:43,916 --> 00:12:45,750
[KANNA]
Does Santa know where we are?

325
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:47,000
Will he really come?

326
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:49,375
[TOHRU] I guess we'll
have to wait and see.

327
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,666
[KOBAYASHI]
I'm exhausted.

328
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:55,333
[KOBAYASHI]
What the crap?

329
00:12:57,750 --> 00:13:00,750
--Merry Christmas!
--Still have some cake left!

330
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:04,083
[KOBAYASHI, TAKIYA panting]

331
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:06,666
[OLD FOLK murmuring]

332
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,125
Are we too late?

333
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:10,666
--[TAKIYA] No, we're good.
--It's just about to start.

334
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:12,208
All right, now the performance

335
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:13,958
of <i>The Little Match Girl</i>
brought to you by

336
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:16,666
the wonderful Oborozuka
Shopping District.

337
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:18,416
Please enjoy the show.

338
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,291
[applause]

339
00:13:22,333 --> 00:13:23,125
The City.

340
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:25,250
It was terribly cold that night.

341
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,625
A light shone upon
the street corner.

342
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:31,083
Standing in that light
was a girl selling matches.

343
00:13:32,375 --> 00:13:33,583
Matches.

344
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,666
Do you want to buy any matches?

345
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:38,916
[SAIKAWA] Unfortunately, no one
wanted to buy her matches.

346
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
[KANNA]
I can't sell any.

347
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:42,583
[SHOUTA]
Umm.

348
00:13:42,666 --> 00:13:44,291
Excuse me, young girl.

349
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:45,708
would you like to buy some hats?

350
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:47,041
Huh?

351
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,583
[SAIKAWA] Before her
appeared an old man selling

352
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:50,791
very strong hats.

353
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:53,125
I'm an old man,
and my old wife made

354
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:54,958
these hats for me to sell.

355
00:13:55,041 --> 00:13:56,541
Oh, they're very strong.

356
00:13:56,625 --> 00:13:58,666
I do not have any money.

357
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:00,291
Are you all right?

358
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:01,291
I'm cold.

359
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:03,291
That must be difficult.

360
00:14:03,375 --> 00:14:05,750
Here, you can burn one
of these to get warm!

361
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:06,750
Burn the hat?

362
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,750
Odd choice since
his wife made it!

363
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:12,375
They're actually
setting it on fire!

364
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:15,125
[SAIKAWA] Then something
unexpected happened.

365
00:14:15,208 --> 00:14:19,916
A strange smoke appeared,
and with it, a suspicious man.

366
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,833
Look, pathetic humans.

367
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,125
Who are you, sir?

368
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:24,833
What do you want?

369
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:26,583
You have been chosen.

370
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:29,458
You will be a magical girl
with a duty to bear.

371
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:31,666
I did not see that one coming.

372
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:34,458
I grant unto you the power
to correct and punish

373
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,208
this corrupt world!

374
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:36,958
Okay!

375
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:38,500
That was quick!

376
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:39,583
Very good.

377
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,541
--Let us go.
--Wait! Me, too!

378
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:42,708
I want to be...

379
00:14:42,791 --> 00:14:44,333
...a magical girl!

380
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:46,708
[FAFNIR] Why do you wish
to be a magical girl?

381
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:49,833
So I can use my power to
commit many nefarious deeds.

382
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:51,500
I need the money, you see.

383
00:14:51,583 --> 00:14:54,250
My wife is very poor and dying
from a terrible sickness!

384
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:57,208
Why wouldn't he just heal her
with his magical power?

385
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:59,333
You would dare voice
your desires like that

386
00:14:59,416 --> 00:15:01,083
without any shame, old man?

387
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:02,375
Acceptable.

388
00:15:02,458 --> 00:15:05,000
You shall be a
magical girl, too.

389
00:15:11,791 --> 00:15:14,083
[SHOUTA]
Oh. This is embarrassing.

390
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:15,666
But, unfortunately,

391
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:19,333
I only have one staff that will
allow you to use your powers.

392
00:15:19,416 --> 00:15:22,375
You will fight, and the
survivor shall have the staff.

393
00:15:22,458 --> 00:15:23,291
Now!

394
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:26,166
[LUCOA]
No, you must not fight!

395
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:28,291
I am a magic fairy.

396
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:31,625
Do not let yourselves be fooled
by that suspicious man's offer.

397
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:32,458
Hmph!

398
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:33,916
[OLD FOLK]
Ooh...

399
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:37,250
I shall not allow you to toy
with the hearts of others.

400
00:15:38,916 --> 00:15:41,625
Leave this to me and go,
little girl and old man girl!

401
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:44,250
No, magic fairy, we cannot
just leave you here.

402
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,416
That's right!

403
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,541
You are so kind.

404
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:48,875
Our time together
was very enjoyable.

405
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:50,750
I shall never forget you two!

406
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:52,250
It was seconds.

407
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:58,125
No way.

408
00:15:58,208 --> 00:16:00,125
Do you know what
we should do now?

409
00:16:00,208 --> 00:16:02,583
A magical girl's role
is to cleanse corruption

410
00:16:02,666 --> 00:16:03,833
from this world, right?

411
00:16:03,916 --> 00:16:05,208
I'm on it!

412
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,750
Where are all the bad
and rotten people?

413
00:16:14,083 --> 00:16:16,791
[SAIKAWA] Incredibly, the spell
cast by the young girl

414
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:20,250
struck a devastating blow
to a nearby mansion.

415
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:22,541
Let's go look over there.

416
00:16:24,958 --> 00:16:28,708
[BOTH] Run, run, run,
run, run, run, run.

417
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:33,083
Are you the two responsible for
setting this place on fire?

418
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:35,458
No, what? Who would
do such a mean thing?

419
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:37,000
[BOTH]
So guilty.

420
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:37,958
I'm very sorry.

421
00:16:38,041 --> 00:16:39,625
I meant nothing ill by it.

422
00:16:39,708 --> 00:16:40,916
It's cool. Don't worry.

423
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,000
I am Kuranosuke Oishi.

424
00:16:43,083 --> 00:16:45,000
Thanks to this fire,
I can easily sneak into

425
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:47,875
the Kira mansion, so you
have my utmost gratitude.

426
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:49,750
What are you doing here?

427
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:51,708
I've come to finally
avenge my lord and claim

428
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:54,541
the head of Kira Kouzuke
No Suke Yoshinaka!

429
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:56,250
Now it's the <i>47 Ronin</i> ?

430
00:16:56,333 --> 00:17:01,375
[TOHRU screams]

431
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:02,625
Avenging your lord?

432
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:04,041
Hilarious!

433
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,791
Prepare yourself, Kira!

434
00:17:05,875 --> 00:17:09,083
If you'd forfeit
your life, come!

435
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,458
She did not just do that!

436
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,458
That's the source
of the corruption.

437
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:14,791
And the enemy of
all magical girls!

438
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:16,375
[yelps] No!

439
00:17:16,458 --> 00:17:19,250
[TOHRU laughs]
No one can beat me in this:

440
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,500
my final and ultimate form.

441
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,708
I'll turn you into dust!

442
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,916
They have to stop
before they lose control!

443
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,166
That's amazing.

444
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:33,291
This must be that CGI!

445
00:17:33,375 --> 00:17:34,583
Ya darn right I'm spry!

446
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:36,583
--[OLD MAN B] No, CGI.
--[ELMA] All right.

447
00:17:36,666 --> 00:17:38,500
[ELMA] Then, I'll have
to get serious, too!

448
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:40,041
[TOHRU]
I dare you!

449
00:18:06,708 --> 00:18:10,750
[applause]

450
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:12,291
[giggles]

451
00:18:13,666 --> 00:18:15,375
What an incredible show!

452
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:23,708
[KANNA]
Kobayashi!

453
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,125
So, what did you think?

454
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:29,166
We were amazing, right?

455
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,458
Uhh.

456
00:18:34,625 --> 00:18:35,875
Yes, you were.

457
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:38,125
I'm proud that you did it
all on your own, too.

458
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:39,375
Good job, Tohru.

459
00:18:39,458 --> 00:18:40,708
Thank you!

460
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:44,333
Does anybody wanna join
me for an after party?

461
00:18:44,416 --> 00:18:45,666
Let's do it!

462
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:48,083
We can take this appreciation
cake they gave us!

463
00:18:48,166 --> 00:18:49,125
Elma.

464
00:18:49,208 --> 00:18:50,708
You just wanna stuff
your face again.

465
00:18:50,791 --> 00:18:52,458
What? That is not at all true.

466
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:53,833
[stomach growls]

467
00:18:53,916 --> 00:18:58,375
[ALL laugh]

468
00:18:58,458 --> 00:18:59,875
[ALL]
Cheers!

469
00:19:19,541 --> 00:19:20,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Ouchie.

470
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:21,875
Where is everyone?

471
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:24,416
They just left to
head to their homes.

472
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,916
Apparently, they're each
having their own,

473
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,125
individual parties, too.

474
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,500
What about Kanna?

475
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:31,750
[TOHRU]
She escorted Miss Saikawa home.

476
00:19:33,958 --> 00:19:35,375
[TOHRU]
Would you like a bath?

477
00:19:35,458 --> 00:19:39,000
Or are you too tired
to mess with that tonight?

478
00:19:39,083 --> 00:19:40,083
Well.

479
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:42,375
Since it's Christmas,
I have an idea.

480
00:19:46,791 --> 00:19:50,000
[yelling, laughing]

481
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:53,291
[KOBAYASHI]
It's beautiful!

482
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:55,041
[TOHRU]
You sure you're not cold?

483
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:56,583
No, I'm great!

484
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:58,500
[TOHRU]
This is unusual.

485
00:19:58,583 --> 00:20:01,291
You've never asked me
to see the view at night.

486
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:02,416
That's weird.

487
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,958
[TOHRU]
Oh.

488
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,208
I almost forgot!

489
00:20:06,291 --> 00:20:07,166
Here!

490
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:08,041
What?

491
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:09,750
Is this Christmas gift for me?

492
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:11,291
[TOHRU]
Yes!

493
00:20:11,375 --> 00:20:14,291
I got you some medicine that
works well for lower back pain.

494
00:20:14,375 --> 00:20:17,000
For real? That's so sweet!

495
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:22,416
[TOHRU] It's a valuable item
in the other world!

496
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:25,250
You grind it down and apply
it to your achy areas.

497
00:20:25,333 --> 00:20:27,208
It works exquisitely!

498
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:28,375
Yeah.

499
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:30,833
Right.

500
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:34,541
Ya know, I was worried
about you all day today.

501
00:20:34,625 --> 00:20:35,458
[TOHRU]
What for?

502
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:37,041
What do you mean?

503
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:38,791
[KOBAYASHI] To be honest,
I was super anxious

504
00:20:38,875 --> 00:20:40,708
while watching your play.

505
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:45,166
Kept worrying if and when I
should jump in to stop you.

506
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:48,375
But then, I realized
everyone loved it.

507
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,916
[KOBAYASHI]
You really did a nice job.

508
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,416
[TOHRU]
Thanks!

509
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,208
[gasps]

510
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:13,500
[TOHRU]
It's a White Christmas.

511
00:21:13,583 --> 00:21:16,666
Here, I sorta got a Christmas
present for you, too!

512
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:19,500
[TOHRU]
Uh? What is it?

513
00:21:19,583 --> 00:21:21,416
Merry Christmas, Tohru.

514
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,291
Enjoy!

515
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:25,875
[TOHRU]
Miss Kobayashi!

516
00:21:25,958 --> 00:21:27,166
[yelps]

517
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:31,750
Tohru, slow down! I'll fall!

518
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:32,916
[TOHRU]
I can't!

519
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,250
[TOHRU giggles]

520
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:47,083
[floor creaks]

521
00:22:00,125 --> 00:22:01,958
[KOBAYASHI]
